<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="163" pageId="3" pageNumber="162" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1852,2058]" lastBlockId="4.[136,1451,158,220]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="163" pageId="3" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,251,1852,1878]" pageId="3" pageNumber="162">Diagnosis</emphasis>
:— 
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="163" pageId="3" pageNumber="162">
It is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[463,754,1852,1878]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Graptopetalum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="superbum">Graptopetalum superbum</taxonomicName>
in sharing a non-caespitose and ramose habit, similar stem length and oblong obovate leaves, but it differs from the latter in having a stem surface smooth vs. squamose, stem diameter 0.7–0.8 vs. 1.0–1.2, leaves per rosettes 31–47 vs. 12–28, leaf color glaucous to brownish green, pinkish when young vs. grey-blue to pink-violet, inflorescence length 9.8–27.5 vs. 30.0–40.0, and branches per inflorescence 5-6 vs. 12-15. It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[432,601,1996,2022]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Graptopetalum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pentandrum">G. pentandrum</taxonomicName>
in stem length with smooth surface and color pattern of petals, but it differs from the latter in having a habit none caespitose ramose vs. caespitose-ramose, rosette diameter 10.0–16.0 vs. 6.0– 
<quantity lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="163" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="162" unit="cm" value="8.0">8 cm</quantity>
, stem diameter 0.7–0.8 vs. 
<quantity box="[469,594,158,184]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="163" unit="cm" value="0.44999999999999996" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.6 cm</quantity>
, leaves 31–47 vs. 12–20, leaf color glaucous to brownish green, pinkish when young vs. blue-green to white blue, branches per panicle 5–6 vs. 3–4.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
